# Never commit operator-specific values (your IP, key-pair name) or Terraform
# state — state contains the AMI id, instance id, and is the source of truth
# for `terraform destroy`. Keep it local or move it to a remote backend (S3
# with DynamoDB lock) when you graduate beyond a personal demo.

terraform.tfvars
*.tfvars
!terraform.tfvars.example

# State + lockfile metadata
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
crash.log
crash.*.log

# Plan output
*.tfplan
